You are applying fixes found by a final whole-branch code review on a Hugo static site homepage redesign, repo at /Users/rod/build/begbie-hugo. You're on git branch `feature/homepage-redesign` (confirm with `git branch --show-current`, don't switch branches, don't create a new branch). Current HEAD is commit 916304e.

Rod (the repo owner) reviewed the findings and approved fixing all five below. Apply all five as a single logical change (you can make one commit or a few small ones, your call, but keep them on this branch).

## Fix 1 (Important): Experience section missing eyebrow + "Where I've led" heading

`themes/portio/layouts/partials/resumeSection.html` currently renders only `{{ .title | markdownify }}` for the section header (from `data/resumeSection.yml`'s `title` field, which is still the old "## My Experience" + a leftover summary sentence about LinkedIn). Every other redesigned section (hero, about, testimonials, writing) pairs a small mono-label "eyebrow" pill above the heading with a tightened display heading — Experience is the only one missing this treatment, and the approved design spec calls this section "Experience — Where I've led."

Read these files first to see the current state:
- `data/resumeSection.yml` (currently has `topTitle: My Resume` and a `title:` markdown block with the old heading/summary)
- `themes/portio/layouts/partials/resumeSection.html` (renders `.resume__heading` with just `{{ .title | markdownify }}`)
- `themes/portio/assets/scss/components/_resume-section.scss` (has `&__heading` but no `&__eyebrow`/`&_eyebrow` rule)

For reference, here's the about section's existing eyebrow pattern to match (same tokens, same visual treatment) — from `themes/portio/assets/scss/components/_about-section.scss`:

```scss
&_eyebrow {
    display: inline-block;
    font-family: $font-mono;
    font-size: $fs-mono-label;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--accent);
    background: var(--accentSoft);
    border-radius: $radius-pill;
    padding: 8px 16px;
    margin-bottom: 20px;
}
```

Do this:
1. In `data/resumeSection.yml`: change `topTitle: My Resume` to `topTitle: Experience`, and change the `title:` field to a tightened heading matching the design spec's naming — use `## Where I've led` (drop the old LinkedIn summary sentence from this field; that content isn't needed here since it's not part of the redesigned section's visual treatment — check whether removing it breaks anything else that reads `.title`, it shouldn't since `resumeSection.html` is the only consumer of this data file).
2. In `resumeSection.html`: add an eyebrow element rendering `{{ .topTitle }}` (a `<span class="resume__eyebrow">{{ .topTitle }}</span>`) directly above the existing `{{ .title | markdownify }}` line inside `.resume__heading`.
3. In `_resume-section.scss`: add a `&__eyebrow` rule inside the `.resume { }` block using the exact same token-driven styling as the about-section pattern shown above (adapt the BEM prefix from `_eyebrow` to `__eyebrow` to match this file's existing `&__heading`/`&__grid`/`&__card` naming convention — this file already uses double-underscore BEM elements, not single).

Accent color must be `var(--accent)`/`var(--accentSoft)` — no hardcoded hex, consistent with every other section on this branch.

## Fix 2 (Minor): Orphaned testimonial-carousel.js

`themes/portio/assets/js/testimonial-carousel.js` is no longer referenced anywhere (removed from the JS bundle concat in `footer.html` back in Task 8, but the source file itself was never deleted). Confirm it's genuinely unreferenced (`grep -r "testimonial-carousel" themes/portio/layouts themes/portio/assets` should show nothing except the file itself), then delete it: `git rm themes/portio/assets/js/testimonial-carousel.js`.

## Fix 3 (Minor): `▶` glyph not marked decorative

In `themes/portio/layouts/partials/hero.html`, the video badge currently has:

```html
<span class="hero_video-badge_label">▶ Watch: {{ .videoLabel }}</span>
```

Wrap just the glyph in a decorative span so screen readers skip it:

```html
<span class="hero_video-badge_label"><span aria-hidden="true">▶</span> Watch: {{ .videoLabel }}</span>
```

## Fix 4 (Minor): Missing comment on `$fs-hero`

In `themes/portio/assets/scss/_tokens.scss`, find the `$fs-hero: unquote("min(6vw, 74px)");` declaration (around line 47, may have shifted slightly). Add a one-line comment directly above it explaining that `unquote()` makes this a non-numeric Sass value, so it cannot be used in `calc()` or other Sass arithmetic — e.g.:

```scss
// unquote() preserves the literal CSS min() function through Dart Sass
// compilation (Hugo's Sass rejects raw px/vw arithmetic). This makes
// $fs-hero a non-numeric string in Sass — do not use it in calc()/arithmetic.
$fs-hero: unquote("min(6vw, 74px)");
```

Adjust the exact comment wording if the surrounding file already has a similar convention, but the content must explain the non-numeric/no-arithmetic constraint.

## Fix 5 (Minor): No `prefers-reduced-motion` guard on animations

This branch added several looping/load-in CSS animations: `blob-morph` and `blob-drift` (in `themes/portio/assets/scss/components/_blob.scss`) are infinite loops; `heroFadeUp` (in `themes/portio/assets/scss/components/_hero-section.scss`) is a one-shot load-in animation used ~5-6 times in that file. Add a `prefers-reduced-motion: reduce` guard so users who've set that OS/browser preference get the animations disabled.

Read both files first to see their exact current structure, then add, near the top of each file (or wherever fits the file's existing organization best), something like:

```scss
@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
  .blob {
    animation: none;
  }
  .blob-wrap {
    animation: none;
  }
}
```

for `_blob.scss`, and for `_hero-section.scss`, either a similar targeted media query disabling the `heroFadeUp`-driven elements, or (simpler and equally correct) a single rule like:

```scss
@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
  .hero * {
    animation: none !important;
  }
}
```

Use your judgment on which is cleaner given the actual file structure — the goal is that `prefers-reduced-motion: reduce` fully disables the blob drift/morph loops and the hero's load-in fade sequence, without needing to touch every individual animation declaration by name.

## Global constraints (apply throughout)

- Accent color always via `var(--accent)`/`var(--accentSoft)` — never a new hardcoded hex.
- No test suite exists — verification is `hugo` build + dev-server check.
- Bootstrap grid classes stay in use for structure (not touched by these fixes, but don't introduce anything that conflicts).

## Verification

After all five fixes: run `cd /Users/rod/build/begbie-hugo && rm -rf public resources/_gen .hugo_build.lock && hugo --quiet` — confirm exit 0, no errors. Then `hugo server -D` briefly and inspect the rendered homepage to confirm: the Experience section now shows an "EXPERIENCE" eyebrow pill above "Where I've led," the video badge's screen-reader-visible text no longer includes the raw triangle glyph name (spot-check via curl/grep of the rendered HTML for the `aria-hidden` wrapper), and grep the repo to confirm `testimonial-carousel.js` no longer exists on disk. For the reduced-motion fix, confirm the media query is present in the compiled CSS output (`grep -c "prefers-reduced-motion" public/scss/style.min.*.css` should be ≥1).

Write your full report to: /Users/rod/build/begbie-hugo/.superpowers/sdd/final-review-fix-report.md — cover all five fixes, what you changed, and verification output for each.

Commit your work (git add the specific files you changed, not `-A`) with one or a few descriptive commit messages referencing this is a final-review fix pass. Reply with ONLY: DONE (or BLOCKED if you hit a real problem) plus the commit SHA(s) and a one-line summary per fix. Do not paste the diff back to me.
